---
/**
 * text-divider Element Documentation
 *
 * Horizontal divider with centered text.
 */
import ElementLayout from '../../../../layouts/ElementLayout.astro';

// Code examples as template strings
const basicCode = `<text-divider>or</text-divider>`;

const formUsageCode = `<form>
  <layout-stack data-gap="m">
    <form-field>
      <label for="email">Email</label>
      <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required />
    </form-field>

    <button type="submit">Continue with email</button>

    <text-divider>or continue with</text-divider>

    <layout-cluster data-justify="center">
      <button type="button">Google</button>
      <button type="button">GitHub</button>
    </layout-cluster>
  </layout-stack>
</form>`;

const sectionUsageCode = `<article>
  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  <p>Introduction content...</p>

  <text-divider>Chapter 1</text-divider>

  <p>Chapter content...</p>
</article>`;

const cssImplementation = `text-divider {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--size-m);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-s);

  &::before,
  &::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    block-size: 1px;
    background: var(--color-border);
  }
}`;
---

<ElementLayout
  title="text-divider"
  description="Horizontal divider with centered text. Use to separate content sections or provide alternative action labels."
  elementName="text-divider"
  category="custom"
  currentPath="/docs/elements/custom-elements/text-divider/"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>text-divider</code> element creates a horizontal line with centered text. Common uses include separating form sections ("or"), chapter markers, and content transitions.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <p>This element has no custom attributes. It's styled purely through CSS.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>

    <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
      <text-divider>or</text-divider>
    </div>

    <h3>Code</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic text divider">{basicCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>In Forms</h2>
    <p>Common pattern for login/signup forms to separate primary and alternative actions.</p>

    <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
      <layout-stack data-gap="m">
        <button type="button">Continue with email</button>

        <text-divider>or continue with</text-divider>

        <layout-cluster data-justify="center" data-gap="s">
          <button type="button" data-variant="secondary">Google</button>
          <button type="button" data-variant="secondary">GitHub</button>
        </layout-cluster>
      </layout-stack>
    </div>

    <h3>Code</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Form with text divider">{formUsageCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Sections</h2>
    <p>Use to mark transitions between content sections.</p>

    <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 30rem;">
      <layout-stack data-gap="m">
        <p>This is the introduction to our guide. It covers the basics you need to know before getting started.</p>

        <text-divider>Chapter 1</text-divider>

        <p>Now we dive into the details. This chapter covers installation and setup procedures.</p>
      </layout-stack>
    </div>

    <h3>Code</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Section divider">{sectionUsageCode}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Variations</h2>
    <p>The text content can be anything meaningful for the context.</p>

    <layout-stack data-gap="l">
      <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
        <text-divider>or</text-divider>
      </div>

      <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
        <text-divider>continue reading</text-divider>
      </div>

      <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
        <text-divider>2024</text-divider>
      </div>

      <div class="example" style="max-inline-size: 25rem;">
        <text-divider>* * *</text-divider>
      </div>
    </layout-stack>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Implementation</h2>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Complete text-divider CSS">{cssImplementation}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The divider is purely decorative - screen readers will read the text content naturally</li>
      <li>Avoid using the divider for critical navigation or structural purposes</li>
      <li>Keep text concise and meaningful</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/hr/">hr</a> - Horizontal rule without text</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/stack/">layout-stack</a> - Vertical stacking</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/form-field/">form-field</a> - Form field wrapper</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</ElementLayout>
